                We can graph this by shading all numbers <var name="$words"/>
                <m><var name="$sol"/></m>. Since the sign in the inequality <var name="$sol[0]"/>
                for <m><var name="$var"/></m> to equal <m><var name="$sol"/></m>, we use a
                <var name="$sol[1]"/> at <m><var name="$sol"/></m>.
              </p>
              <image>
                <latex-image>
                  \begin{tikzpicture}
                    \begin{axis}[numberline, xlabel={\($var\)}]
                      \addplot[$sol[2]] coordinates {($sol[3],0) ($sol,0)};
                    \end{axis}
                  \end{tikzpicture}
                </latex-image>
              </image>
              <p>
                We read the graph from left to right to tell us the interval notation for the
                solution set: <m><var name="$interval"/></m>.
